title: For Sale/Trade:  Aircrew Body Armor Plates and Carriers
postcontent:
For sale or trade:  several sets of 1980's vintage aircrew body armor carriers with plates.

Do you need personal protection during these uncertain times?  Don't have thousands to spend on new plates and a carrier?  I offer an affordable and functional solution.

  These armor sets were commonly referred to, by helicopter air crews, as "chicken plates".  They are capable of protecting against multiple hits from 7.62mm caliber weapons.  I have experimented with a few sets and found that they can sustain multiple hits from 5.56mm and even 6.5mm rounds, without penetrating the inner layers.

  The plates are ceramic with what I think is a Kevlar outer-layer and the edges are protected with rubber guards to prevent damage.

  The carriers aren't anything special, just padded O.D. green cotton/nylon with button fasteners on the shoulder straps and a Velcro cummerbund.  They are not like the newer types of carriers with PALS webbing, but they work very well with tactical vests and chest rigs.

  These plates are quite heavy compared to more contemporary styles, but they weren't designed for lots of mobility.  I estimate a complete set to weigh around 20 lbs.  A healthy adult male wouldn't have any problem wearing these for extended periods.  Those of you who remember the old "Ranger Body Armor", will be familiar with the weight and wear-ability of this armor, as the two are very similar.

  I acquired these plates and carriers from a DRMO warehouse in Germany about 5 years ago.  These sets are no longer issued to active duty units.  They have been stored indoors since I received them and have been handled carefully during moves.  There are slight cosmetic variances between the sets, but all appear to be serviceable.

  The plates WILL fit in some newer plate carriers.

  They aren't pretty or as cool as newer systems, but they DO stop bullets and are much more affordable than new styles.

    I have multiple sets of sized medium and large.  

  $100 OBO.  See trade options.  Additional photos available upon request.

title: For Sale/Trade:   Survival Kit (Cold Weather), Individual
location: Springfield, Lorton, Newington, Ft. Belvoir, Northern Virginia, Virginia
postcontent:
Individual survival kit issued to Army air crews for cold and temperate environments.  These kits were salvaged from a DRMO warehouse in Germany a few years ago and have been stored in my climate-controlled basement since then.

The kit includes a heavy-duty O.D. green nylon case with metal zippers, nylon carry handle, and yellow shoulder straps.  Ideal for storing in your vehicle for emergencies.  Retention lanyards and hooks allow the pack to be fastened in place.  Weight is about 15lbs.  Dimensions are approximately 15"x15" and 5" deep.  

Inside the nylon carry case is an cotton duck pouch with an aluminum container that protects most of the contents and serves as a frying pan and water collection method.  Kits include the following items:

1 x laminated, pocket size Dept. of the Army Technical Manual (instructions and care).
1 x mosquito head net
1 x camouflage poncho
100' nylon "550" parachute cord
1 x orange scarf (for signaling)
1 x 5qt. water storage bladder (NOT a Camelbak!)
1 x saw-knife-shovel tool (can handle small trees)
5 x general purpose survival food packet (basically high-calorie energy bars:  all in original packaging and unopened.  No indications of spoilage or contamination).
5 x candles in sealed aluminum cans
1 x individual first aid kit in its own self-contained storage box.  various dressings, bandages, iodine tablets, and minor first-aid items).
1 x survival fishing kit (razors, spoons, weights, strings, hooks, etc.)
1x emergency signaling mirror
1 x 25' of snare/trapping wire
1 x wire saw (useful on metal, wood, and plastic)
1 x magnetic survival compass (plastic).
1 x whistle
1 x fishing gill-net
1 x stainless survival pocket knife
1 x knife sharpener
1 x magnesium fire starter
1 x "sparklite" fire starter
1 x foil survival blanket

NOTE:  these kits once contained pyrotechnic items, flammable items, and sleeping bags.  These items were removed by DRMO personnel in Germany and are not included with the kits.  The kits contain many useful items and have enough room for additional items.  If emptied, the kits would make an affordable "bug-out" bag, tool kit, camping gear storage, or general purpose kit bag.

Kits are sold as is and I deny any responsibility for misuse.  Use at your own risk.

$50ea. Additional photos available upon request.

title: For Sale:  Nazi Stamped FN 1922
postcontent:
This is a very nice example of a Nazi stamped FN 1922 (10/22) from early war. The serial lacks a prefix so it was manufactured early in the war before Germany captured the FN plant in Belgium. It does have a Eagle stamp above the serial number on the barrel, one on the frame and one on the slide. Also there is a Waa140 on the barrel locking block. I tried capturing the markings on my camera but it is poor quality and hard to see, but they are there. All numbers on this are matching. Finish is 92%+ No import marks There are purposeful notches on the grip The mag is original FN (these were not numbered) .32acp No pitting on gun or in bore, there is a small amount of frosting at bore rear opening, overall bore condition is 90%+ 6 digit serial with no prefix - this is a early gun Functionality is perfect and smooth - never had a jam and fired multiple different ammo types.
